From 67964bd165342b01e14f23e8f811bf1bbeb20e41 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Claude (via BandSea's request)" <claude@anthropic.local>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 08:18:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: correct stratification, unification regression,
 aggregate-cycle detection

- Restore correct stratified evaluation by computing one stratum per SCC
  of the true dependency graph (graph_compute_strata, reusing the existing
  Tarjan pass in semantic_validator.c), replacing both the old per-rule
  self-reference heuristic (which could give a copy-rule P :- P_impl_N a
  lower stratum than P_impl_N itself) and v1.2's flat unordered fixpoint
  (unsound for negation: this engine has no fact retraction, so a rule
  can permanently commit a fact based on an incomplete view of what it
  negates, depending on rule list order).

- Fix a unification regression in apply_rule_general/apply_rule_arithmetic:
  a variable occurring in both a positive and a negative atom (the normal
  shape of stratified negation) was unconditionally rejected instead of
  having its negative-atom occurrences deferred to the negation-check
  block. Made the positive-occurrence lookup order-independent instead of
  assuming locations[0] is positive.

- Add EDGE_DEFINED_BY_AGGREGATE to the SCC dependency graph in
  semantic_validator.c: a negative cycle closed through an aggregate
  dependency was previously invisible to Tarjan and silently accepted as
  stratifiable.

- Fix O(V*E) Tarjan (find_node_index did an O(V) scan per edge) back down
  to O(V+E) via an index stamped on each Node.

- Fix float->int UB (result==(int)result evaluated before the magnitude
  guard) by checking magnitude first.

- Unify the previously-inconsistent fixed buffer sizes (16 vs 32) onto
  shared SUPERLANG_MAX_BODY_ATOMS/MAX_ARITY constants, and reject in
  type_checker.c (compile time) any rule that would exceed them, instead
  of silently truncating or overflowing a stack buffer at runtime.

- Fix config loading silently dropping input facts of arity >= 4 by
  loading through the existing array-based add_fact_direct instead of
  config_add_fact's varargs 1/2/3 switch.

- Test infra: run_semantic_tests.sh now asserts actual expected output,
  not just exit codes (it previously reported PASS on test3/test4 while
  printing wrong answers). Removed tests/run_tests.sh (referenced the
  wrong directory and stale filenames; fully superseded by
  run_semantic_tests.sh + run_valgrind_all.sh). Added test10 (negative
  cycle through an aggregate) and test11 (4-level negation chain).

Verified: 12/12 semantic tests with real value assertions, 12/12 valgrind
clean (0 errors, 0 leaks), all existing examples still run, clean -Wall
-Wextra build.
